Command.Name: setBoilerPlateTestPathAndFileName
Command.Description: Changes the path and file name for the boiler plate test script.

Command.Name: setRootTestFolderPath
Command.Description: Changes the root path of the test workflow definitions.

Command.Name: setDefaultTestBehavior
Command.Description: changes a configuration to control if the default test command behavior is to run all tests or not.

Command.Name: setSlowExecutionConfiguration
Command.Description: Sets a configuration flag to enable or disable slow test execution.

Command.Name: setMultiTestExecutionConfiguration
Command.Description: Enable or disable test generation for single or multiple test commands.

Command.Name: setBrowsersList
Command.Description: Sets the configuration setting that contains the list of browsers to test with.

Command.Name: setExecutionEngine
Command.Description: Sets the execution engine that should be used when executing the tests.

Command.Name: setEnableReporterConfiguration
Command.Description: Sets a configuration flag to enable or disable report generation after test execution.

Command.Name: setReportPathConfiguration
Command.Description: Sets the output path on the local system where the test report should be saved.

Command.Name: setChildProcessLimitTime
Command.Description: Sets the test process timeout time before the test will automatically fail.

Command.Name: setCmdType
Command.Description: Sets the shell, console, or terminal for test execution: OS native shell, DOS CMD, Powershell, or Bash.

Command.Name: test
Command.Description: Executes a test, or suite of tests.
